summary: REQ-1 and REQ-3 appear implemented via new Practice question-number navigator UI and year-selection flow for PYQ categories, and backend data model/migration adds an optional year field. However, the diff summary provides no evidence of the required backend seeding/idempotent population of NEET-syllabus chapters and year-tagged PYQ questions (REQ-4). Several additional UI/auth/profile/contributor/admin related changes appear beyond the BuildRequest.

missing_requirements.requirement: Populate the app with NEET-syllabus-based chapters for Physics, Chemistry, and Biology, and populate the NEET/JEE PYQ banks with year-tagged questions for years 2025–2000 (idempotent seeding; valid MCQ fields).
missing_requirements.reason: Diff shows a schema/migration update to support question.year, but does not show any seed data being added nor any idempotent seeding logic that creates NEET syllabus chapters and year-tagged PYQ questions across 2025–2000 on fresh deployment.
evidence: backend/main.mo (truncated; shows type additions but no seeding shown)
backend/migration.mo (only sets year = null; no seed content)
